text.section:
The Committee consists of the following 6 members:
the Secretary of Transportation or a designee;
the Secretary of General Services or a designee;
the Secretary of Public Safety and Correctional Services or a designee;
the President of Blind Industries and Services of Maryland or a designee;
the Assistant Secretary for Vocational Rehabilitation within the State Department of Education or a designee; and
the Secretary of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation or a designee.

The Committee shall:
establish procedures to govern procurement of supplies and services from community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses;
from the State procurement list, choose appropriate supplies and services for community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses to offer for procurement;
provide that the State procure those supplies and services from a community service provider or an individual with disability owned business;
if supplies or services are not available for procurement from a unit of the State government, determine whether supplies or services are available from a community service provider or an individual with disability owned business;
determine the fair market price of supplies and services that community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses provide;
in accordance with market conditions, adjust prices for the supplies and services that community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses provide; and
at the request of a community service provider or an individual with disability owned business, review and, if appropriate, change the price of a supply or service.

In addition to the duties specified under subsection (e) of this section, the Committee shall:
establish and periodically review eligibility policies or guidelines for participating community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses;
maintain a current list of community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses;
periodically review and revise its list of community service providers and individual with disability owned businesses; and
send any revised list to the Secretary of General Services who shall make the list available to each person responsible for buying supplies or services for the State or a State aided or controlled entity.
